### Failure Mode 3: Member Removal with Unresolved Assignments

- **Risk**: MEDIUM
- **Code Location**: GroupMetadataManager.java (member removal logic), GroupCoordinatorShard.java (deleteGroups method ~line 269)
- **Description**: When a member is removed from a group (via LeaveGroup or timeout), the current test coverage doesn't verify that partial or in-flight partition assignments are correctly cleaned up. If a member's target assignment record exists but hasn't been applied (current assignment not yet updated), removing the member without cleaning up the target assignment can cause the partition to remain unassigned or cause conflicts when another member joins.
- **Proposed Test**:
  ```java
  @Test
  public void testMemberRemovalWithPendingTargetAssignment() throws Exception {
      GroupMetadataManagerTestContext context = new GroupMetadataManagerTestContext.Builder()
          .build();

      String groupId = "test-group";
      String memberId1 = Uuid.randomUuid().toString();
      String topicName = "test-topic";

      // Create consumer group with member
      context.replay(
          new ConsumerGroupMetadataValue()
              .setGroupId(groupId)
              .setState(ConsumerGroupState.STABLE.toString())
      );

      // Add first member with subscription
      ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData joinRequest = new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(memberId1)
          .setMemberEpoch(0)
          .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(5000)
          .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of(topicName))
          .setTopicPartitions(List.of());

      CoordinatorResult<ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> joinResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.consumerGroupHeartbeat(requestContext(), joinRequest);

      // Verify target assignment created
      assertTrue(context.hasTargetAssignment(groupId, memberId1));

      // Member leaves before current assignment is applied
      LeaveGroupRequestData leaveRequest = new LeaveGroupRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .addMember(new LeaveGroupRequestData.MemberIdentity()
              .setMemberId(memberId1)
          );

      CoordinatorResult<LeaveGroupResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> leaveResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.leaveGroup(requestContext(), leaveRequest);

      // Verify all target assignments for the member are removed
      assertFalse(context.hasTargetAssignment(groupId, memberId1),
          "Target assignment should be cleaned up when member leaves");

      // Verify group can be deleted without issues
      DeleteGroupsResponseData.DeletableGroupResultCollection deleteResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.deleteGroups(requestContext(), List.of(groupId));

      assertEquals(Errors.NONE.code(), deleteResult.iterator().next().errorCode());

      context.close();
  }
  ```
- **Coverage Delta**: This test exercises the member removal path in GroupMetadataManager.leaveGroup() and validates cleanup of both current and target assignments. It hits the record generation logic that creates tombstone records for ConsumerGroupTargetAssignmentMemberValue.

