### Failure Mode 6: Authorization Bypass in Concurrent Member Operations

- **Risk**: MEDIUM
- **Code Location**: GroupCoordinatorService.java (request routing), GroupCoordinatorShard.java (all group methods)
- **Description**: Each group operation (heartbeat, offset commit, etc.) should be authorized. However, existing tests only verify authorization at the GroupCoordinatorService level in isolated cases. There's no test ensuring that when authorization fails for one member's operation, concurrent operations from other members don't bypass authorization or corrupt the group state. This could allow unauthorized consumers to peek at group state or commit offsets.
- **Proposed Test**:
  ```java
  @Test
  public void testAuthorizationEnforcedConcurrentlyAcrossMembers() throws Exception {
      GroupMetadataManagerTestContext context = new GroupMetadataManagerTestContext.Builder()
          .withAuthorizer(new MockAuthorizer())
          .build();

      String groupId = "test-group";
      String authorizedMember = Uuid.randomUuid().toString();
      String unauthorizedMember = Uuid.randomUuid().toString();
      String topicName = "test-topic";

      // Authorized member joins
      ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData authorizedJoin = new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(authorizedMember)
          .setMemberEpoch(0)
          .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(5000)
          .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of(topicName))
          .setTopicPartitions(List.of());

      RequestContext authorizedContext = requestContext(ApiKeys.CONSUMER_GROUP_HEARTBEAT)
          .withPrincipal("authorized-user");

      CoordinatorResult<ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> authorizedResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.consumerGroupHeartbeat(authorizedContext, authorizedJoin);

      assertTrue(authorizedResult.response().errorCode() == Errors.NONE.code() ||
          authorizedResult.response().errorCode() == Errors.REBALANCE_IN_PROGRESS.code());

      // Unauthorized member attempts to join simultaneously
      ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData unauthorizedJoin = new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(unauthorizedMember)
          .setMemberEpoch(0)
          .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(5000)
          .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of(topicName))
          .setTopicPartitions(List.of());

      RequestContext unauthorizedContext = requestContext(ApiKeys.CONSUMER_GROUP_HEARTBEAT)
          .withPrincipal("unauthorized-user");

      // Set up authorizer to deny this principal
      context.authorizer().denyOperation("unauthorized-user", groupId);

      assertThrows(
          Exception.class,
          () -> context.groupMetadataManager.consumerGroupHeartbeat(unauthorizedContext, unauthorizedJoin),
          "Unauthorized member should be denied access"
      );

      // Verify authorized member's state is unchanged
      ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData pollRequest = new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(authorizedMember)
          .setMemberEpoch(authorizedResult.response().memberEpoch());

      CoordinatorResult<ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> pollResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.consumerGroupHeartbeat(authorizedContext, pollRequest);

      assertNotNull(pollResult.response().memberEpoch(),
          "Authorized member should still be in group after unauthorized member's denial");

      context.close();
  }
  ```
- **Coverage Delta**: This test exercises authorization enforcement across concurrent operations in GroupMetadataManager by validating that authorization failures in one operation don't affect other concurrent operations or corrupt group state.

